15/03/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government declared Sunday (14 March) a national day of mourning for the victims of the terrorist attacks in Madrid. 
At least nine Romanians were killed in Thursday's blasts aboard commuter trains. 
Two dozen others remain hospitalised. 
Romania is joining all EU member states in observing three minutes of silence Monday for the 200 victims.
Greece too will observe the moments of silence. 
The government issued an official statement condemning the attacks "in the most unequivocal manner". 
(Rompres - 15/03/04; ANA, MPA - 14/03/04; Rompres - 13/03/04)
